gomodel:SYNGO_4768  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"we analyzed the recruitment of two endogenous endosome markers, Rab5 and EEA1, towards GFP-2x-FYVE puncta. Here, we analyzed the fraction of GFP-2x-FYVE/Rab5 double positive puncta as a measure for early endocytic vesicles, and the fraction of GFP-2x-FYVE/Rab5/EEA1 triple positive puncta as a measure for early endosomes (Figure 5A).\n\nFor technical reasons this analysis was performed along axons without an additional co-staining for synapses. Of note, co-localization studies with Synaptophysin demonstrated that at least 65% of GFP-2x-FYVE positive puncta along axons were synaptic (Figure 4, figure supplement 2D and E), a concept previously reported at the Drosophila NMJ (Wucherpfennig et al., 2003). Therefore our analysis represents a mixture of PI3P-positive organelles in- and outside synapses.\"\n\nHere, GFP-2x-FYVE was used as a reporter for PI3P. Figure 5 shows fewer endosome proteins (EEA1, Rab5) were recruited towards PI3P-positive organelles along axons lacking Piccolo. Figure 5 figure supplement 1C/F showed PI3P/Rabex5/Rab5 triple-positive staining, suggesting Rab5 and Rabex5 were localized to endosomes at the presynapse. This is reduced in axons lacking Piccolo.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampi were harvested from Pclo(wt/wt) and Pclo(gt/gt) (Wistar) P0-2 rats of either sex\" p.23\n\nAntibody anti-Rabex5 (rabbit polyclonal) Thermo scientific RRID:AB_11157010 (1:100)\n\nnote; selected the protein sequence that matches the mouse swissprot record (linked in antibody manufacturer's website)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4768" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

